## **Commands (exact flags)**

### **1 ŌĆö test-site** (preserve destination env files)

```powershell
robocopy "F:\project_workspace\mosc-temp" "F:\project_workspace\event-site-front-end-test-site" /E /XD .git .claude /XF .env.local .env.production
```

| Flag | Meaning |
|------|---------|
| `/E` | Copy subdirs, including empty |
| `/XD .git .claude` | Never overwrite destination Git or Claude dirs |
| `/XF .env.local .env.production` | Do **not** overwrite destination env secrets |

### **2 ŌĆö template** (no env exclude in the userŌĆÖs usual command)

```powershell
robocopy "F:\project_workspace\mosc-temp" "F:\project_workspace\event-site-front-end-template" /E /XD .git .claude
```

- Prefer adding `/XF .env.local .env.production` on template too unless the user **explicitly** wants env files mirrored.
- Env files must still **never be committed** (secret filter + `.gitignore`).

### **Robocopy exit codes**

| Code | Meaning | Treat as |
|------|---------|----------|
| 0 | Nothing copied | OK |
| 1ŌĆō7 | Files copied / extras / mismatches | **Success** for this workflow |
| Ōēź 8 | Failures | **BLOCKER** ŌĆö stop before commit |

```powershell
# After each robocopy:
if ($LASTEXITCODE -ge 8) { throw "robocopy failed with exit $LASTEXITCODE" }
```

